# AC Mitsubishi project rules

## Architecture

- All Modbus I/O lives in `custom_components/ac_mitsubishi/modbus.py` — **zero HA imports**, independently testable.
- All polling lives in `custom_components/ac_mitsubishi/coordinator.py` via `DataUpdateCoordinator`.
- Entities **never** poll directly; they read from `self.coordinator.data`.
- Climate entity inherits `CoordinatorEntity`.
- Power on/off: `switch.py` — same device as climate; writes `REG_POWER` via coordinator.
- Config entries only — no YAML setup.
- All I/O is `async`. No blocking calls in the event loop.

## const.py

- No business logic. Register addresses, mode maps (`HVACMode` / fan / swing), and tuning constants go here.
- `INTEGRATION_VERSION` must stay in sync with `manifest.json` (see `.cursor/rules/versioning.mdc`).

## coordinator.py

- Raises `UpdateFailed` (not raw exceptions) from `_async_update_data` when the unit is unreachable.
- Opens one Modbus TCP session per poll cycle; reads registers; closes connection.

## modbus.py

- Uses `asyncio.open_connection` — no external Modbus library.
- Modbus **RTU framing** over raw TCP (no MBAP header); CRC-16 on frames.

## Naming conventions

- Domain: `ac_mitsubishi`
- Device identifiers: `{(DOMAIN, entry.entry_id)}`
- Config entry title: `AC Mitsubishi v{INTEGRATION_VERSION} ({host})`

## Tests

- `tests/test_modbus.py` — frame/CRC helpers, no HA fixtures where possible.
- `tests/test_climate.py` — maps and `ACState` behavior.
- Mock Modbus at the `ModbusRTUClient` level in coordinator tests, not at raw socket level.

## Deploy

- Credentials come from `.env.ha` (gitignored); never hardcode.
- PowerShell: avoid `&&` — use separate lines or `;`.
- WSL key handling lives in `deploy-ha-wsl-bootstrap.sh`.
